Another for distress from vomiting. Take 2 ounces of yeast from wheat, 1 dram each of cloves, mastic and myrrh and enough very strong vinegar to make a cataplasm for the stomach and put it warm on the stomach on a linen cloth as large as the stomach one hour before the meal. You should know that nothing so improves the stomach that does not retain food. It comforts it very wonderfully.

